HEADWORD: Frenzied
<hw>Fren"zied</hw> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧n"z⟦icr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos>
<def>Affected with frenzy; frantic; maddened.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Fren"zied*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The people <qex>frenzied</qex> by centuries of oppression.</q>
